On 13 June 2025. Country: India. State: Manipur. Town: Imphal East. Text: Property destruction: On 13 June 2025, a joint team of central and state security forces (likely police based on their presence in the region) dismantled a temporary camp set up by suspected cadres of an underground militant group during a search operation in the Baruni Hills of Imphal East district (coded to Porompat town, Imphal East, Manipur) amidst ongoing violence between Meitei and Tribal communities in the state. Several items were also recovered including radio sets, some without antennas and microphones, handheld wireless sets without batteries, wireless set batteries, covers, dry cell batteries, a repeater, multiple wireless antennas, LAN cable, batteries, an inverter, a solar charger converter, solar panels, cable wires, and a cabinet box.
